JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma paid a visit to the Soweto home of the late Winnie Madikizela-Mandela on Wednesday. Zuma said he was shocked to hear of the struggle stalwart's passing. READ: Graça Machel lauds Winnie's 'extraordinary life', mourns her passing He described Madikizela-Mandela as an inspiration. "Her bravery to face the enemy was beyond understanding," he told journalists waiting outside. Madikizela-Mandela died in hospital on Monday. Watch Zuma's full address in the video below. eNCA